  "commentary": "With SPX spot at 6997.25 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (18.5B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any move above 7000 as they're long gamma and need to hedge delta. The PIN regime confirms dealers will provide liquidity against directional moves, creating strong resistance at the 7000-7025 zone where over 27B in positive gamma creates a selling wall. Key levels to watch are 6875 (GEX flip) as the line in the sand and 7000 as the immediate resistance ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get capped around 7000 with downside support building toward 6875.",
